name: Todd Kowalski
bio: I'm from Winnipeg Canada, I love drawing, painting, and music. I'm working hard trying to make the most out of my life while it's still here.

social_posts.post_text:
Behold THE KOWALSKI!
My great buddy David ‘The Beaver’ Guillas from @strange_earth_guitars created this magical axe for me. It has 7 strings, fanned frets and is made from reclaimed wood with a natural marigold finish and is fitted with Bare Knuckle pick ups! It sounds amazing and suits the way I play perfectly. 
 One thing we never would’ve predicted is that my kitty, Willy, seems to like the taste of marigolds and has licked the finish right off with his scratchy little tongue. Oh well, I probably would’ve done the same thing eventually if I got hungry enough. 
Anyway, we knew it would be a tasty guitar!
The Kowalski logo is the stylistic equivalent of wearing sweatpants to the school dance. We couldn’t let the axe get TOO nice!
#guitar #handmadeguitar #guitarplayer #guitarsofinstagram #thekowalski

Lately my bro @quiquegaros and I have been doing daily Photoshop paintings to help build our skills. This is of Rovinj, Croatia. 
#digitalart #digitalpainting #landscape #rovinj #croatia

My friend @quiquegaros and I have each been doing a 50 minute Photoshop painting every night to try to improve our skills. It’s always fun to hang loose and see what we can make without worrying about it too much, it’s also a good time to try a bunch of new things. This is painting #25. 
 Thanks for looking!
#digitalart #digitalpainting #dailypainting #paintingpractice #photoshop

This is one of 4 pictures I did last week in a class with Joaquin Belisario @muim_saj @warriorpainters 
This was done using the lasso and full opacity hard round brush. It’s fun working like this and being forced make really clear decisions. I’m having a really good time in the class.
Winnipeggers will probably recognize the location.

#digitalpainting #winnipeg #lasso #digitalart #landscapepainting #warriorpainters

I was sketching a bit last night and sort of liked this guy. Haha
#character #characterdesign #sketching #sketch #boxing #blahblah

This is a plein air gouache painting from last summer. I was riding my bike around looking for something to paint and saw this simple little scene at Bruce Park. I really liked the vibrancy of the colours and tried to capture them. ‘Twas a good time. Ha. Thanks for looking!
#pleinairpainting #gouache #gouachepainting #urbansketching #landscape #winnipeg

I had a fun time painting at The Forks here in Winnipeg this weekend. It’s Pride month so the festivities were rolling. I like seeing people happy, being themselves and having fun and I find all the colours and different ways people are dressing a refreshing change after the long grey winter. Overall it was a great weekend! 
On a side note, to me painting beige in in the shade one one the hardest colours to get looking right but sometimes stuff like that catches my eye and I end up giving it a crack.
Thanks for looking, stay cool!
#urbansketching #sketching #sketch #pridewinnipeg #pridewinnipeg2023 
#gouachepainting #gouache #pride @knapsackcoffee

social_posts.post_text:
This is a little gouache painting I did in St. Boniface. Painting outside is fun, I like cruising around on my bike until something catches my eye! I’ve certainly noticed a lot of things I wouldn’t have thought about if I wasn’t painting. 
Thanks for looking! 
#pleinair #pleinairpainting #gouache #urbansketching #stboniface

Lia was looking colourful at Patricia Beach this weekend so I took a crack at painting her while we chilled. Winter is so long and cold here in The Peg that I really do appreciate every warm day we get and I love being outside!

#pleinair  #pleinairpainting #patriciabeach #landscapepainting 
#sketch #gouache #gouachepainting

This is a painting from Pine Point Rapids from a couple weeks ago. I don’t get much of a chance to paint this type of thing from life so the water may look a little el dorko but it was fun. Hopefully I’ll get another try sometime soon. Have a great one everybody! 
#pinepointrapids #gouache #gouachepainting #landscapepainting #landscape

The other day my friend was talking about a flat front assignment we did quite a while ago in Will Weston’s class. This is mine, I never ended up posting it anywhere so I thought I’d slap it up here now for fun. I really love drawing stuff like this! (swipe to see the whole thing)
#visdev #visualdevelopment #design #sketching #drawing #environmentdesign #goodtimes

Last week I took a crack at painting White Mouth Falls out in The Whiteshell. I’m still trying to figure out how to translate the chaos and layers of the water into painting, I’ve gotta try again soon. It’s always nice to get out of the city to walk around and paint a little bit. Have a good one! 
#whitemouthfalls #gouache #gouachepainting #pleinair #pleinairpainting #landscapepainting #sketching

This is a painting from way out of the pier in Gimli, Manitoba. I’ve never painted a boat or marina before but it seemed like a nice step up from alleys and garbage cans in Winnipeg.  I had a very enjoyable day cruising around with Lia and I hope to get back out there at least one more time before the cold returns.
The painting was a fun challenge, 
Thanks for looking, have a great weekend!
#pleinair #pleinairpainting #gouache #gouachepainting #sketching #landscapepainting

Here’s a few wall textures from a props class I took with @willwestonstudio quite a while back! That was a lot of fun!
